<br>
There are some good tanks out there and some pretty crappy ones too.  Therefore, it's not always guaranteed that you will have the luxury of BS the whole fight.  The line I find myself repeating in group over and over again is "SAME DAMMED SIDE PLEASE".  It seems that monks now don't want to side with the tank because they get hit more often, and I even had a bard tell me once that they got more lag on that side of the mob /boggle<br>
<br>
So it all boils down to you.  The rogue is an extremely versatile character and you can do almost anything in this game.  Defining a role for yourself is limiting and to a certain extent, insulting.  Sometimes you end up tanking - oh well.  It happens.  Sometimes the main tank can't hold his aggro, sometimes the monk wants to do the CR and sometimes the bard won't let anyone scout but him.  To each his own.<br>
<br>
I firmly believe that there is no other class in the game that adds as much to the group as we do.  It's all in how you flexible you want to be.  I carry 3 weapons on me - and will switch them in and our depending on how good the other melees are.  If the cleric is having to dump all his mana on you, then you are to blame - no the other tanks in the group. It is your job to be on the opposite side of the main tank, not his to try to be on the other side of you. If you are getting aggro then you back up to max melee range, evade, stop attacking for a few seconds, or even switch weapons.  <br>
<br>
And sometimes you have to pull if you are the highest level character in the group in order to minize adds.  If you have not explored sneak pulling you are truly missing out.  I have pulled in Velks, Howling Stones, Seb and Chardok and I think we as a class can do a dammed good job pulling.<br>
<br>
Only you can control what you bring to the group.  It is NOT based on gear, it is not based on how maxed this skill is and that skill is.  It is based on how well you not only know but understand your abilities.  <br>
<br>
One last thing - if your defense is not maxed, I would work on that.  It is silly to have *ANY* of your melee skills not be maxed. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68709 > <b> <i>Kalynn Taranis</a> </B></i>
