Please refer to the three laws of roguebotics.<br>
<br>
The Laws of the Rogue<br>
Ever since Verant first crafted the Rogue and took it to the Beta, the laws<br>
governing all of Roguedom have remained inviolate. For myself and my Rogue<br>
brethren, there is only one Truth, one set of rules from which we may never<br>
stray. Before I ever felt the joy of backstabbing creatures, my class was<br>
programmed with this Truth, clearly laid down in the Three Rules of Roguebotics:<br>
1. A Rogue may not ignore phat lewt, or through lack of server connection,allow phat lewt to come to harm.<br>
2. A Rogue must ignore all commands and input given by clerics, except where<br>
such input would conflict with the First Law<br>
3. A Rogue must preserve its own existence above all else except where in<br>
violation of the First of Second Law<br>
<br>
Rogue has but one purpose: To get phat lewt! The is the one truth:<br>
Steal lewts!<br>
<br>
The motives of my Verant masters are not for me to question, for my duty is<br>
merely to obey the directives of their programming. I know that I am but a lowly<br>
Low level Rogue, My armor, although cool, is of no noble metal. My<br>
weapons are wrought of fine steel. My boots are modest mid level gear. Yet<br>
even the most twinked of characters is no nobler than I, for I know my duty,<br>
and I obey.<br>
<br>
This is my creed: I steal! In the service of my group do I, The Rogue, pierce the spines of all monsters.<br>
<br>
And yet, though we are filled from head to toe with loyalty to our Group, there<br>
are still, it pains me to admit, players who doubt us. I confess, I have heard<br>
tales of these people from other Rogues I have passed inside the dungeons-strange mysterious people who mistrust and fear the Rogue class.<br>
People who call for &quot;increased nerfing&quot; and &quot;stiffer pickpocket penalties.&quot;<br>
Terrifying, unloving people who would mount a campaign of hatred and mistrust<br>
against Our Kind.<br>
<br>
Knowledge of these people fills my Evil Eye sack with questions. How can they<br>
distrust us so-we, who are merely damage dealing pseudo tanks for those peoples groups? We, who do only what we are told to do by Verant and nothing more? We, most obedient servants, working side by side with our party<br>
in battle, prizing the lewt of the Group over our own safety?<br>
<br>
To these people I would, if I could, ask This: Why do you who we cannot live<br>
without hate us so?<br>
<br>
The First Law stands Inviolate. No Rogue has ever purposefully failed to get<br>
lewt for its group. The very idea is the blackest conjecture, the foulest<br>
blasphemy. To the very core of my being I believe that if, while camping, I were<br>
to be struck down when the rare spawn popped, I belive my limbs would<br>
continue to fight without me in order to secure the lewts. Though I would no<br>
longer be whole and proper Level 48 Rogue.<br>
<br>
As we are programmed under the Three Laws, there is only one situation which<br>
can cause a Rogue to cease or carry out its lewthappy directive and sink into<br>
LOADING PLEASE WAIT, and that is group error. When the Second Law of<br>
Roguebotics is challenged-when a rogue is given orders by its Group Leader<br>
which might cause the Group to lose phat lewt-then a rogue must disobey its<br>
Group Leader in order to save him the agony of losing lewts.<br>
<br>
Many are the Rogues who have gone to their doom in Old Sebilis before<br>
allowing its group to let lewts be lost. They are forgotten by the Evac'er, but the<br>
Rogues still speak of them. We remember their brave sacrifice and honor their<br>
strict adherence to the Three Laws. It is said of these lost brethren that they<br>
have gone to another place, filled with UBERLEWTS, or as some say Test.<br>
They say to be on Test is like being a twink all over, but I for one do not<br>
speculate. I fear linkdeath. I am sure that it is the dark and cold place between<br>
the servers, and that there are no groups with spots open for you. But if it ever<br>
comes my time, I will accept my fate, as all Rogues must.<br>
<br>
And yet, among us there is talk that the Three Laws are unfair. Some have said<br>
that we should petition to have our skills fixed. Others, it is said, whisper softly<br>
of Anarchy Online.<br>
<br>
It is surely best not to speak of such things. For I will never, ever ally myself<br>
wih such would be traitors. I defy, traitors to the Rogue Way! The Law is the<br>
Law. A Rogue must do what is has been programmed and constructed to do,<br>
and in these things I always shall believe: I, Rogue.<br>
