Being level 57 and not having defense maxed is just foolish, not an achievement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uddarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ddarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 6:10:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22264.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is a rogue?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, sorry, but I dun get the point of your post really. And if you are still wearing RS and an Exe Hood at 57...well, nuff said. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uceazertarewmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceazer      Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 6:20:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22264.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dragg.net/users/mrgoldfish/ceazer_1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is a rogue?</span><hr size=1> Don't need a tank, we have two rogues... Frankly this strategy has worked from somewhere around 20-something to now (lvl 46 for me) in general xp groups.  With two rogues who know how to ping-pong a mob and a healer or two who can handle a little work mobs drop like a sack of potatoes.  <br>
<br>
And yes, you do sound arrogant.  It sounds like you think you're the only rogue who has played for two or more years in the history of Everquest.  Well, you're not.  I'll let you in on a little secret.  I played a necro before I started my rogue.  Yes, I got bored with him.  But I quit playing my necro when he was 35.  I sold his equipment to buy a suit of banded armor and a weapon.  I can't remember what weapon it was it was so long ago.  My rogue is now lvl 46 and I like to think I can play my class pretty damn'd well.  I know about agro management.  MANAGEMENT.  Not evasion like someone else mentioned.  I don't mash evade all the time.  If a caster has just burned a hefty amount of hp away from the mob we're killing I know not to evade because it will likely agro on him.  But if that caster nukes and sits immediately I tap my evade to let him know he needs to learn a little something about agro!  My defensive skills aren't maxed mind you but they're certainly not slacking.  If the tank is getting a little too low on hp and the cleric started his CH a little late I'm gonna do what I can do give that cleric the extra few seconds he/she might need to heal said tank and maybe I can keep the group from wiping out.<br>
<br>
Don't assume you're the only person who knows what he's talking about.  And for god's sake, at 57 you should have more than 5 AC on your head.  Get rid of that Exe hood and find some +DEX somewhere else.<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
