<br>
I always stand opposite the main tank. This allows me to maximize my damage output and grab the agro if the main tank is getting low on hp. My equipment is not great, but I can take some damage while the cleric is medding. <br>
<br>
I don't evade unless I have to much agro. There is no point. A good taunter can keep the mobs attention enough for nearly all my backstabs to be at the back of the mob. By the time my backstab recycles, the main tank will most likely have regained the mobs attention. <br>
<br>
There are lots of players that don't understand our capabilities, and have to be reminded constantly that they need to keep the mobs back to us. Usually these are alt-melee classes (Monks, Rangers, SK's). They just don't understand that this is for the benefit of the group. I say, if you don't want to get hit during melee, then maybe you should be a caster. Enough said on that subject.<br>
<br>
About the equipment issue. Some people don't have the connections, time or patience to go get uber-plane armor or whatever is better than Ravenscale. Weapons on the other hand are a little more important. I can understand this, but there are some limitations to this as well. Not everybody can get that super-uber items. <br>
<br>
The skill thing however is an issue where I must insist on being maxxed. I think that we are short changing ourselves if we don't get defense up to max shortly after leveling. What happens if you are on a Dragon Raid and you are sticking away at the dragons hind quarters. He/she gets really ticked and decides to tell you about it and your defense skills are 10 levels below your current level. You are really dead, really fast. That may be an extreme example, but you get the idea. If you are constantly evading and ducking out of combat, you will suffer. The group will suffer also, because when you stop attacking, you may miss a few hits on the mob that may put it down when the cleric is oom and the main tank is at 10% hp. This could spell doom in a close fight.<br>
<br>
If I think of anything else, I will stick my 2cp in here again. Thanks for the ear. <br>
<br>
<br>
